cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR, cs.IR

The paper focuses on using deep neural networks for extracting road user trajectories from drone footage, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of drones for data collection and the focus on naturalistic behavior also suggests a potential fit for robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of data-driven methods for automated vehicles, which could potentially fall under computer networks and security (cs.CR) or information retrieval (cs.IR) if the focus is on data collection and analysis.
